lf you are a real Champagne lover, this may be the only page of our catalogue that you want to read. We understand. It’s difficult to stop looking at all those tempting bottles. For our part, it's more difficult still to imagine the holidays without the magnificent Champagnes of Moét & Chandon. Their illustrious wines make a Serious claim to the summit of Champagne per- fection. From the colossal Salamanazar—holding the equiva- lent of a full twelve-bottle case of Brut Impérial—to the elfin split of White Star Extra Dry, every style and every size is a profound statement of Moét’s historic commitment to the con- tinued excellence of the most famous wine in the world.

Here at the left is one of the grandest bottles of wine generally available in the world today—a 270 oz. Salamanazar of Moét’s elegant Brut Impérial—their beautiful, bone dry non-vintage Champagne ($167.49 the bottle, one to a case). Next is an irresistible magnum of what may be the world’s greatest Champagne—Dom Pérignon. Caviar, foie gras, truffles, Dom Pérignon—all expressions of gastronomic perfection ($52.89 the magnum). On the right are three sizes of Moét’s charming “White Star” extra-dry Champagne. For those who prefer the Champagne less dry than ‘brut,’ this delicious wine is an ideal choice.

All these bottles don’t tell the full story of the many superb Champagnes of Moét & Chandon. We take distinct pride in Presenting below a full range of these celebrated wines.
